<body>
    <h1>Error Handling</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"ErrorHandling-ErrorMessageStructure">Error Message Struct=
ure</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
=09"result": {
=09=09"errors": [
=09=09=09{
=09=09=09=09"code": 101,
=09=09=09=09"message": "Component not found",
=09=09=09=09"details": "Unable to find component for {componentId}"
=09=09=09}
=09=09]
=09}
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Error Property</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Mandatory</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Code</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">YES</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">A specific API code used to identify the type of=
 error. This is not the HTTP Code.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Message</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">YES</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">A consumer friendly description of the error wit=
h context if appropriate. I.e. 'Invalid customer number' (explicit error)&n=
bsp;or 'Missing mandatory field' (implicit - i.e. general due to provider n=
ot providing further information)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Details</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">NO</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Detailed message of the error, usually derived f=
rom provider error message for business related errors. This could be pass =
through or filtered if sensitive information is returned.<br>
 For technical errors this will be defined in the API implementation.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>All errors should be returned in JSON format. Westpac Mesh APIs can resp=
ond with a single or multiple errors.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ErrorHandling-ErrorClassification">Error Classification</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Error Cassification</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">HTTP Status Code</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Error Code</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Business Error</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">4xx</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">1 - 9999</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Related to data processed by the API, an error w=
ith consumer input</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Technical Error</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">500</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">10000 or greater</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Related to the environment, typically out of the=
 consumer's control</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Process for Mapping Errors</strong></p>
<p>It is the responsibility of the API Designer to work with the Business A=
nalyst to agree on which provider errors are 'business important'.<strong><=
br></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Confirm whether errors being returned are actual errors and not warning=
 or informational messages</li>
<li>If no errors, return a HTTP response code 2xx</li>
<li>If the error is bad data submitted by the consumer, return HTTP respons=
e code 4xx</li>
<li>If the error was caused by failed processing on the server, return HTTP=
 response code 5xx</li>
<li>Once the appropriate HTTP response code is determined, identify the app=
ropriate error code</li>
<li>If none are appropriate, assign a new error code&nbsp;in the error bloc=
k by allocating the next available number based on the error classification=
 (business or technical)</li>
<li>Provide an easily understood description of the error in the message el=
ement of the error block</li>
<li>Map the provider's error message to the details element of the error bl=
ock</li>
</ul>
<p>When designing the errors in your API, put yourself in the shoes of a co=
nsumer and think about the types of errors you would want to know about.</p=
>
<p>It is important that the occurrence of an error is propagated up the cal=
l stack, but the error detail at each level must NOT be blindly propagated =
up the call stack.&nbsp;You can include provider error details from the dow=
nstream call in your API's specific error block to aid in troubleshooting.<=
/p>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Further reading:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/API+Erro=
r+Handling">API Error Handling</a></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
